==============================================================================

SpectraMind V50 — .gitignore (Paired with .dvcignore, Mission-Grade)

——————————————————————————

Purpose:

• Keep Git history clean: commit only code, configs, and DVC pointers

• Prevent committing large artifacts/data; DVC manages data & models

• Mirror .dvcignore intent while adding Git-specific exclusions



Notes:

• Always commit: dvc.yaml, dvc.lock, *.dvc, .dvc/config (no secrets here)

• Data/models: store blobs in DVC remote, keep pointers (*.dvc) in Git

• Kaggle has no internet; never rely on remote pulls in kernels

==============================================================================

───────────────────────── Core DVC/Git Safety ─────────────────────────

Keep DVC control & pointers tracked

!.dvc/
!.dvc/config
!.dvc/config.local
!.dvcignore
!dvc.yaml
!dvc.lock
!*.dvc

Ignore DVC runtime internals (DVC also auto-writes its own .gitignore under .dvc/)

.dvc/cache/**
.dvc/tmp/**
.dvc/experiments/**
.dvc/logs/**
.dvc/plots/tmp/**
.dvc/state
.dvc/updater

───────────────────────── Data / Models (Git) ─────────────────────────

Blobs live in DVC remote; keep pointers (*.dvc) only

data/**
models/**

but never ignore the DVC pointer files themselves

!/.dvc
!*.dvc

